(3156, 334, 'faq_2_faq_number', '03'),
(3157, 334, '_faq_2_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3158, 334, 'faq_2_faq_title', 'How is child custody determined in Ontario? '),
(3159, 334, '_faq_2_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3160, 334, 'faq_2_faq_description', 'Child custody in Ontario is determined based on the best interests of the child. The court considers factors such as the child\'s needs, relationships with parents, and ability to care for the child.\r\n'),
(3161, 334, '_faq_2_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3162, 334, 'faq_3_class', ''),
(3163, 334, '_faq_3_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3164, 334, 'faq_3_faq_number', '04'),
(3165, 334, '_faq_3_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3166, 334, 'faq_3_faq_title', 'How is child support calculated in Ontario? \r\n'),
(3167, 334, '_faq_3_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3168, 334, 'faq_3_faq_description', 'Child support in Ontario is calculated based on the paying parent\'s income and the number of children. The province has set guidelines that determine the amount of support based on income brackets.'),
(3169, 334, '_faq_3_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3170, 334, 'faq_4_class', ''),
(3171, 334, '_faq_4_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3172, 334, 'faq_4_faq_number', '05'),
(3173, 334, '_faq_4_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3174, 334, 'faq_4_faq_title', 'How is spousal support determined in Ontario? \r\n'),
(3175, 334, '_faq_4_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3176, 334, 'faq_4_faq_description', 'Spousal support in Ontario is determined by considering factors such as the length of the marriage, the financial needs of each spouse, and their ability to support themselves. The Spousal Support Advisory Guidelines provide guidance on the amount and duration of support.'),
(3177, 334, '_faq_4_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3178, 334, 'faq_5_class', ''),
(3179, 334, '_faq_5_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3180, 334, 'faq_5_faq_number', '06'),
(3181, 334, '_faq_5_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3182, 334, 'faq_5_faq_title', 'Can custody and support orders be changed? \r\n'),
(3183, 334, '_faq_5_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3184, 334, 'faq_5_faq_description', 'Yes, custody and support orders can be changed if there has been a significant change in circumstances. You can request a modification through the court.'),
(3185, 334, '_faq_5_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3186, 334, 'faq_6_class', ''),
(3187, 334, '_faq_6_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3188, 334, 'faq_6_faq_number', '07'),
(3189, 334, '_faq_6_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3190, 334, 'faq_6_faq_title', 'What\'s the difference between separation and divorce? '),
(3191, 334, '_faq_6_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3192, 334, 'faq_6_faq_description', 'Separation is the process of living apart, while divorce is the legal termination of a marriage. You can be legally separated without getting a divorce.\r\n'),
(3193, 334, '_faq_6_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3194, 334, 'faq_7_class', ''),
(3195, 334, '_faq_7_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3196, 334, 'faq_7_faq_number', '09'),
(3197, 334, '_faq_7_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3198, 334, 'faq_7_faq_title', 'How long does it take to get a divorce in Ontario? '),
(3199, 334, '_faq_7_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3200, 334, 'faq_7_faq_description', 'The time it takes to get a divorce in Ontario varies depending on the complexity of the case and court availability. On average, it can take several months to a year or more to complete the process.\r\n'),
(3201, 334, '_faq_7_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3202, 334, 'faq_8_class', ''),
(3203, 334, '_faq_8_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3204, 334, 'faq_8_faq_number', '10'),
(3205, 334, '_faq_8_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3206, 334, 'faq_8_faq_title', 'Should I hire a family lawyer? '),
(3207, 334, '_faq_8_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3208, 334, 'faq_8_faq_description', 'While not mandatory, hiring a family lawyer is highly recommended, especially for complex family law matters. A lawyer can provide legal advice, guide you through the process, and protect your rights and interests.'),
(3209, 334, '_faq_8_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3210, 334, 'faq_9_class', ''),
(3211, 334, '_faq_9_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3212, 334, 'faq_9_faq_number', '11'),
(3213, 334, '_faq_9_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3214, 334, 'faq_9_faq_title', 'Can I represent myself in family court? \r\n'),
(3215, 334, '_faq_9_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3216, 334, 'faq_9_faq_description', 'Yes, you have the right to represent yourself in family court. However, family law can be complex, so it\'s advisable to seek legal advice or assistance if possible.'),
(3217, 334, '_faq_9_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3218, 334, 'faq_10_class', ''),
(3219, 334, '_faq_10_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3220, 334, 'faq_10_faq_number', '12'),
(3221, 334, '_faq_10_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3222, 334, 'faq_10_faq_title', 'What are the alternatives to going to court for resolving family law issues? '),
(3223, 334, '_faq_10_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3224, 334, 'faq_10_faq_description', 'Mediation, negotiation, and collaborative family law are alternative dispute resolution methods that can help resolve family law issues without going to court. These methods encourage cooperation and finding mutually acceptable solutions.'),
(3225, 334, '_faq_10_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3226, 334, 'faq_11_class', ''),
(3227, 334, '_faq_11_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3228, 334, 'faq_11_faq_number', '13'),
(3229, 334, '_faq_11_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3230, 334, 'faq_11_faq_title', 'How is property divided during a divorce in Ontario? '),
(3231, 334, '_faq_11_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3232, 334, 'faq_11_faq_description', 'In Ontario, property division is based on the principle of equalization. Generally, each spouse is entitled to an equal share of the value of assets accumulated during the marriage, excluding certain exemptions.'),
(3233, 334, '_faq_11_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3234, 334, 'faq_12_class', ''),
(3235, 334, '_faq_12_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3236, 334, 'faq_12_faq_number', '14'),
(3237, 334, '_faq_12_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3238, 334, 'faq_12_faq_title', 'Can I get a restraining order to protect myself or my children? '),
(3239, 334, '_faq_12_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3240, 334, 'faq_12_faq_description', 'Yes, you can apply for a restraining order, also known as a protection order, if you or your children are at risk of harm from another family member. The court will assess the situation and issue an order if necessary.'),
(3241, 334, '_faq_12_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3242, 334, 'faq_13_class', ''),
(3243, 334, '_faq_13_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3244, 334, 'faq_13_faq_number', '15'),
(3245, 334, '_faq_13_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3246, 334, 'faq_13_faq_title', 'What rights do grandparents have in Ontario? '),
(3247, 334, '_faq_13_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3248, 334, 'faq_13_faq_description', 'Grandparents in Ontario do not have automatic legal rights to visitation or custody of their grandchildren. However, they can seek court intervention if it\'s in the best interests of the child to maintain a relationship with the grandparents.'),
(3249, 334, '_faq_13_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3250, 334, 'faq_14_class', ''),
(3251, 334, '_faq_14_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3252, 334, 'faq_14_faq_number', '16'),
(3253, 334, '_faq_14_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3254, 334, 'faq_14_faq_title', 'What is the age of majority for child support in Ontario? '),
(3255, 334, '_faq_14_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3256, 334, 'faq_14_faq_description', 'In Ontario, child support generally continues until the child turns 18 or completes their education if they are still dependent.'),
(3257, 334, '_faq_14_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3258, 334, 'faq_15_class', ''),
(3259, 334, '_faq_15_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3260, 334, 'faq_15_faq_number', '17'),
(3261, 334, '_faq_15_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3262, 334, 'faq_15_faq_title', 'What factors does the court consider when making custody and access decisions?'),
(3263, 334, '_faq_15_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3264, 334, 'faq_15_faq_description', 'The court considers various factors, including the child\'s best interests, the ability of each parent to care for the child, the child\'s wishes (depending on their age and maturity), and the history of care and involvement of each parent.'),
(3265, 334, '_faq_15_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3266, 334, 'faq_16_class', ''),
(3267, 334, '_faq_16_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3268, 334, 'faq_16_faq_number', '18'),
(3269, 334, '_faq_16_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3270, 334, 'faq_16_faq_title', 'What is the process for adopting a child in Ontario? '),
(3271, 334, '_faq_16_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
(3272, 334, 'faq_16_faq_description', 'The adoption process in Ontario involves assessments, background checks, and court hearings. It\'s important to consult with an adoption professional or agency to understand the specific requirements and steps involved.'),
(3273, 334, '_faq_16_faq_description', 'field_64a55b659ff95'),
(3274, 334, 'faq_17_class', ''),
(3275, 334, '_faq_17_class', 'field_64a55b289ff92'),
(3276, 334, 'faq_17_faq_number', '19'),
(3277, 334, '_faq_17_faq_number', 'field_64a55b2d9ff93'),
(3278, 334, 'faq_17_faq_title', 'Can same-sex couples get married and divorced in Ontario? '),
(3279, 334, '_faq_17_faq_title', 'field_64a55b369ff94'),
